tripled its revenue to  million from  million between  and  innodata acquired isogen international in  and integrated both of the company’s content management and publishing technologies structured information standards and outsourcing services in  the name of innodata isogen inc was formally adopted by the company starting in  the company started taking advantage of the growing popularity of ebooks to become a producer of technology and processes for transforming books into ebook formats for distribution and sellthrough on tablets and ereaders innodata has produced over  million ebooks and is distributing more than  ebooks per day across  global platforms and ebookstorescitation needed innodata advanced data solutions iadsedit in  the company launched a new segment innodata advanced data solutions to develop products designed to help companies outside the information and publishing industries adapt to the public’s rapid adoption of digital and mobile devices within this segment they started two new subsidiaries synodex and docgenix in  the company changed its name back to “innodata” this move became official on june   when innodata’s stockholders approved an amendment to the company’s certificate of incorporation to change the company’s name from “innodata isogen inc” to “innodata inc” in july  innodata acquired mediamiser ltd “mediamiser” a media monitoring and analysis company based in ottawa ontario canada that provides software and professional services for public relations and marketing professionals in december  innodata acquired intellectual property and related assets of bulldog reporter a pr company providing pr industry newsletters journalist databases media intelligence and professional development programs referencesedit  its all about digital enablement  innodata inc innodatacom   innodata inc nasdaqinod quotes  news  google finance googlecom   innodatas annual report pdf innodata  retrieved  april    innodata isogen inc announces name change to innoda